parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Rear Main Seal Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear main seal can cause the engine to lose oil, leading to engine failure, stalling, and loss of power, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially on busy highways.
Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to premature engine failure, increased emissions, and decreased fuel efficiency, which can result in costly repairs and potential safety risks.
Timing chain failure can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to PCV Valve Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: PCV valve failure can cause the engine to fail, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
Solenoid failure can cause the engine to fail to start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
